I"h	<p>A drawing contains nothing but graphical elements:</p>

<ul>
  <li>rectangle</li>
  <li>ellipse</li>
  <li>line</li>
  <li>text.</li>
</ul>

<p>Each element contains:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x,y)</code> coordinate of centre point</li>
</ul>

<p>Rectangle contains:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x,y)</code> coordinate of centre point</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(0,0)</code> is that the top-left of the canvas</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(w,h)</code> width and height of rectangle (e.g. top = x-w/2, bottom = x+w/2)</li>
  <li>shape attributes</li>
</ul>

<p>Ellipse contains:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x,y)</code> coordinate of centre point</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(0,0)</code> is that the top-left of the canvas</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(w,h)</code> width and height of ellipse</li>
  <li>shape attributes</li>
</ul>

<p>Line contains:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x1,y1)</code> start point</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x2,y2)</code> end point</li>
  <li>path points <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x,y)</code>â€™s excluding <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x1,y1)</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x2,y2)</code></li>
  <li>line attributes</li>
</ul>

<p>Text contains:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(x,y)</code> of top-left corner</li>
  <li>attributes</li>
  <li>text attributes</li>
</ul>

<p>Attributes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>color</li>
</ul>

<p>Shape Attributes</p>
<ul>
  <li>Attributes</li>
  <li>thickness (outline thickness, default=1)</li>
</ul>

<p>Line attributes</p>

<p>Text Attributes</p>
<ul>
  <li>Attributes</li>
</ul>

<h1 id="di">DI</h1>
<p>DI means Design Intent (often called Architecture)</p>

